{"questionId":"11233","questionHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Which of the following can be both formed from bromoethane and converted directly into ethanal?</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">CH<sub>3</sub>CH<sub>2</sub>Br → <strong>X</strong><br><strong>X</strong> → CH<sub>3</sub>CHO</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">A. CH<sub>3</sub>CH<sub>2</sub>OH</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">B. CH<sub>3</sub>OCH<sub>3</sub></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">C. CH<sub>3</sub>COOH</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">D. H<sub>2</sub>C=CHBr</span></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>A</p>","meta":{"questionId":"11233","referenceCode":"19M.1.sl.TZ2.25","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Which of the following can be both formed from bromoethane and converted directly into ethanal? CH3CH2Br → XX → CH3CHO A. CH3CH2OH B. CH3OCH3 C. CH3COOH D. H2C=CHBr","paper":"1","level":"sl","questionNumber":"25","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 10: Organic chemistry","10.2 Functional group chemistry","Core","Topic 10: Organic chemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}